1+2\epsilon+3\epsilon^{2}+\cdots+n\epsilon^{n-1}=-\frac{n}{1-\epsilon}
1+2\epsilon+3\epsilon^{2}+\cdots+n\epsilon^{n-1} = f'(\epsilon)
f(x)=1+x+x^2+\cdots+x^n= \dfrac{x^{n+1}-1}{x-1}
f'(x)=\dfrac{(n+1)x^n(x-1)-(x^{n+1}-1)}{(x-1)^2} 
f'(\epsilon)=\dfrac{(n+1)(\epsilon-1)-(\epsilon-1)}{(\epsilon-1)^2}=\dfrac{n}{\epsilon-1}
\epsilon\neq 1
\epsilon=1
